Bio

The House Of Krazees comprised of Hektic, Mr. Bones and The R.O.C. They released Home Sweet Home, on their own record label imprint, Asylum Records. Released locally in October of 1993, Home Sweet Home had a print run originally of about 500 copies made and sold. Despite having virtually no recording budget and minimal experience, Home Sweet Home was well received by their peers and local Detroit audiences. This album also sampled heavy metal songs by acts such as Metallica, Alice In Chains, and Ozzy Osbourne.
